Malta Guinness, Nigeria’s most loved, non-alcoholic, premium malt drink joined the Emir of Kano; HRH Aminu Ado Bayero, ably represented by the Assistant Secretary – ‎Kano Emirate, Abass Awaisu Sanusi and other illustrious dignitaries to celebrate the just concluded Sallah. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-827525 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/EID-2.jpg" alt="" width="1000" height="667" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/EID-2.jpg 1000w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/EID-2-300x200.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px"> The two-day long Eid-el-Kabir celebration was full of special prayers and festivities with Malta Guinness making a presentation of drinks to the Emirate to commemorate a successful Eid and reinforce its commitment to enabling Nigerians everywhere enjoy every moment. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-827526 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/EID-3.jpg" alt="" width="668" height="498" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/EID-3.jpg 668w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/EID-3-300x224.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 668px) 100vw, 668px"> On another colourful note, the Malta Guinness brand was present at the reopening of the Kaduna-Abuja Railway Station within the week, to refresh and refuel travellers with Ice-cold Malta Guinness as they made their way home to reunite with their families for the holidays. With Malta Guinness, sharing goodness, energy and vitality comes naturally, even at such significant moments. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-827527 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/EID-4.jpg" alt="" width="924" height="612" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/EID-4.jpg 924w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/EID-4-300x199.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 924px) 100vw, 924px"> Speaking to the role of Malta Guinness, Ifeoma Agu, Senior Brand Manager, Adult Premium Non-alcoholic Drinks, Guinness Nigeria explains, “Malta Guinness continues to celebrate and fuel the greatness of Nigerians. <img class="aligncenter wp-image-827528 size-large" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/EID-5-Copy-1024x977.jpg" alt="" width="740" height="706" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/EID-5-Copy-1024x977.jpg 1024w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/EID-5-Copy-300x286.jpg 300w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/EID-5-Copy-1536x1466.jpg 1536w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/EID-5-Copy-2048x1954.jpg 2048w" sizes="(max-width: 740px) 100vw, 740px"> We love being part of significant cultural celebrations and milestones in Nigeria while encouraging our Consumers to enjoy every occasion with Africa’s No.1 Premium non- alcoholic malt drink- Malta Guinness, which is packed with energy giving B-vitamins to give you that ‘top of the world’ feeling” <img class="aligncenter wp-image-827529 size-full" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/EID-6.jpg" alt="" width="924" height="612" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/EID-6.jpg 924w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/EID-6-300x199.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 924px) 100vw, 924px"> For more details about Malta Guinness, follow @maltaguinnessng on Instagram and Twitter and on Facebook: www.facebook.com/maltaguinness.